cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with robustness verification for neural networks, specifically Transformers, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the importance of different words in sentiment analysis, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
